item.description: 1 year sober âœ¨ Iâ€™ve thought about this moment so much over the last year and whether Iâ€™ll even make it. Firstly, I never ever thought Iâ€™d say Iâ€™m a year without alcohol. I was that person who said they would just never stop drinking. I was the reliable drunk friend who would never say no to a midday drink on a Wednesday. I was the girl who had shots of whatever was in the cupboard at 10am if I was going to meet someone new, and the person who didnâ€™t remember how they got home, who they made out with and whether or not they had sex. I drank when I was happy, sad, lonely, angry, celebrating, depressed, anxious. I would ask the doctor if I could drink on antibiotics and would google what alcohol is good for a sore throat. I made jokes about how much I drank, and how I â€˜neededâ€™ a wine after a hard day. I got drunk on first dates, at family gatherings, alone on a Monday night. Alcohol was my comfort. Red wine on a flight, vodka on a night out, gin in the summer, mulled wine in the winter. Wet pussy shots I made myself to pour into my friends mouths in the hope theyâ€™d get as drunk as me. Yet no one ever said I was an alcoholic. I thought it wasnâ€™t a problem because I didnâ€™t wake up in the morning and have vodka with breakfast. But what I did do was fall asleep in clubs, pass out while having sex and wake up with anxiety so bad, the only way to cure it was with alcohol. Itâ€™s been a lot of work to get here, and Iâ€™ll probably talk about it more in a YouTube video some time because thereâ€™s just so much I want to say ğŸ˜… I wanna say thank you to @holly who wrote the book that got me through the first month, to my sober friends @sarhyspage and @worthlesstwink who I think of every time I think about drinking, to my friends and family (especially Pazzy) who have respected, understood and stood by me the past year. And most of all, my absolute soul sister Emma who inspired me to stop drinking in the first place and inspires me every day to be the best version of myself I can ğŸ’• I could go on and on, but mostly posting this here I just hope maybe I can inspire someone to make a change you never thought you could.
